<exercise checkit-seed="0003" checkit-slug="TI6" checkit-title="Partial fractions">
    <statement>
        
        <p>
            Consider the partial fraction decomposition <me> \frac{3 \, x + 7}{x^{2} + 3 \, x + 2}=-\frac{1}{x + 2} + \frac{4}{x + 1}.</me>  Use this decomposition to compute <m>\displaystyle\int \frac{3 \, x + 7}{x^{2} + 3 \, x + 2}dx</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>\displaystyle\int \frac{3 \, x + 7}{x^{2} + 3 \, x + 2}dx=\displaystyle\int -\frac{1}{x + 2} + \frac{4}{x + 1}dx=-\log\left(x + 2\right) + 4 \, \log\left(x + 1\right)+C.</me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
